<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-366-840  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 366 840.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Design  June 8 1989 v37 n12 p27(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Optoelectronic scheme opens doors for neural nets.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Till, Johna.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An optoelectronic approach to networking may revolutionize neuralcomputing.andP;  The approach is more flexible and promises to buildhardware neural networks that are more complex than previousneural networks.andP;  The complexity of the model that can beimplemented is determined by the number of interconnections in thenetwork.andP;  The optoelectronic approach could allow designers toconstruct systems from neural network integrated circuits and toupgrade the network models without having to change the hardware.andO;The approach takes advantage of the fact that photons do notinteract with each other.andP;  The density of the opticalinterconnections can therefore be much greater than even the mostadvanced silicon and gallium arsenide processes.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     New TechniqueOpticsElectronicsNeural Networks.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   The optoelectronic approach for neural networks. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>